Install/Uninstall instruction for the Geeklog recaptcha plugin.

INSTALL:

Step 1:  Uncompress the recaptcha plugin archive while in the <geeklog_dir>/plugins directory.  The archive will
create a directory called recaptcha in the plugins directory.

Step 2:  Create the admin directory.  Under your admin/plugins/ directory, create a directory called recaptcha.

Step 3:  Change to your <geeklog_dir>/plugins/recaptcha/ directory.  Copy the files in the admin directory 
to the admin/plugins/recaptcha/ directory your created in step 2.

Step 4:  Log in to your Geeklog as a root user and go to the plugin editor.  Click on the install link of the recaptcha plugin and it will be installed.

Step 5:  Go to the configuration editor and click on recaptcha.  Enter reCAPTCHA API Public Key and Private Key that you obtain at "https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin/create".

UNINSTALL:

Step 1:  Log in to your Geeklog as a root user and go to the plugin editor.  Click on the uninstall link of the recaptcha plugin and it will be uninstalled.

Step 2:  Delete the two plugin directories created in the install process:  <geeklog-dir>plugins/recaptcha/ and <admin>/plugins/recaptcha/.

That's it.
